import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='net_generation', data=data, hue='source', ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend of net generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation')
    plt.legend(title='Source', loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='source', y='net_generation', hue='renewable', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of renewable energy sources?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Energy Source')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation')
    plt.legend(title='Renewable', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    source_net_generation = data.groupby('source')['net_generation'].sum()
    plt.pie(source_net_generation, labels=source_net_generation.index, autopct='%.2f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of net generation by source?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title="Sources", loc="upper right")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='net_generation', y='renewable', hue='source')

    plt.legend(title='Energy Source', loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data = data.pivot_table(index='year', columns='source', values='net_generation', aggfunc='sum')
    data = data.fillna(0)
    
    plt.stackplot(data.index, data.T, labels=data.columns)
    plt.title("What is the trend of net generation by source over the years?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Year")
    plt.ylabel("Net Generation")
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
